        "accordion_how_to_use": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "HOW TO USE",
            "content": "<p>Chew one piece of gum for 5 minutes, up to twice daily. Do not swallow the gum. Do not exceed the recommended daily dose.<br/><br/>Suitable for vegetarians and vegans. Made without most major allergens (milk, eggs, fish, shellfish, tree nuts, peanuts, soy). Gluten and gelatin free.</p>",
            "open_by_default": true,
            "clinical_drawer_button_text": "",
            "clinical_drawer_title": "",
            "clinical_drawer_body": "",
            "clinical_drawer_bg_color": "#ffffff",
            "clinical_drawer_text_color": "#080b2b"
          }
        },
        "accordion_benefits": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "BENEFITS",
            "content": "<p>✔ Boosts Nitric Oxide production at the oral level<br/>✔ Restores beneficial oral bacteria for a balanced microbiome<br/>✔ Supports circulation, energy and recovery<br/>✔ Freshens breath without sugar or artificial fillers</p>",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "clinical_drawer_button_text": "Clinical Trials",
            "clinical_drawer_title": "Clinical Trials",
            "clinical_drawer_body": "<p>Only a small percentage of dietary supplements are tested in gold-standard human clinical trials. <strong>Berkeley Life® Nitric Oxide Support</strong> has been evaluated in double-blind, placebo-controlled research demonstrating its ability to increase nitric oxide bioavailability in humans. The dietary nitrate ingredients used in our formulation are supported by a growing body of peer-reviewed clinical research validating improvements in vascular function, endothelial health, and blood pressure regulation.</p><h3>The Impact of Clinical Proof</h3><p>Double-blind, placebo-controlled trials (DBPCTs) are considered the gold standard in scientific research because they help ensure:</p><ul><li><strong>Bias elimination</strong></li><li><strong>Control for placebo effect</strong></li><li><strong>Validated efficacy</strong></li><li><strong>Safety and tolerability assessment</strong></li></ul><p>By studying the full nitrate formulation as it is consumed, Berkeley Life® ensures the product is evaluated for real-world effectiveness and safety—not just theoretical ingredient benefits.</p><h3>Nitric Oxide Production</h3><p>Berkeley Life® is formulated to increase nitric oxide through the <strong>dietary nitrate → nitrite → nitric oxide pathway</strong>. Unlike L-arginine-based supplements, this pathway remains active even when endothelial nitric oxide synthase (eNOS) declines with age.</p><ul><li><strong>Clinical Trial Results:</strong> In a double-blind, placebo-controlled study, participants taking Berkeley Life® demonstrated significant increases in salivary nitrite and plasma nitrite compared to placebo. Test strip readings correlated with laboratory measurements, confirming improved nitric oxide bioavailability.</li></ul><h3>Vascular & Endothelial Health</h3><p>Nitric oxide is essential for healthy blood vessel function. It supports vasodilation, circulation, and endothelial integrity—all of which naturally decline with age.</p><ul><li><strong>Clinical Trial Results:</strong> In clinical research evaluating dietary nitrate supplementation over 12 weeks, participants showed improvements in endothelial function and reductions in carotid artery stiffness, a recognized marker of cardiovascular risk.</li></ul><h3>Blood Pressure Support</h3><p>Nitric oxide helps relax and widen blood vessels, supporting healthy blood pressure regulation.</p><ul><li><strong>Clinical Trial Results:</strong> Clinical studies of dietary nitrates have demonstrated improvements in systolic blood pressure and vascular responsiveness compared to placebo, particularly with consistent daily use over 8–12 weeks.</li></ul><h3>Energy & Oxygen Efficiency</h3><p>Nitric oxide plays a critical role in oxygen delivery and mitochondrial signaling. Healthy nitric oxide levels support efficient energy production and muscle performance.</p><ul><li><strong>Clinical Research Findings:</strong> Research on dietary nitrates has shown improvements in oxygen utilization and exercise efficiency, including reduced oxygen cost during physical activity.</li></ul><h3>Aging & Nitric Oxide Decline</h3><p>Nitric oxide production naturally declines with age due to oxidative stress, hormonal shifts, and reduced enzyme activity. Berkeley Life® provides a nitrate-based pathway that supports nitric oxide production independently of age-related enzymatic decline, offering measurable vascular support as the body’s natural production decreases.</p>",
            "clinical_drawer_bg_color": "#ffffff",
            "clinical_drawer_text_color": "#080b2b"
          }
        },
        "accordion_ingredientes": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "INGREDIENTS",
            "content": "<p><strong>Potassium Nitrate</strong><br/><br/>Fuels beneficial oral bacteria that convert dietary nitrates into Nitric Oxide —supporting healthy blood flow and energy from the very first chew.<br/></p><p><strong>Probiotic Blend<br/></strong><br/>Restores balance to the oral microbiome, helping reduce harmful bacteria, freshenbreath, and keep the Nitric Oxide pathway working efficiently.<br/></p><p><strong>Vitamin C & Zinc</strong><br/><br/>Antioxidant and mineral support that protects Nitric Oxide molecules and helpsmaintain healthy gums and circulation.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "clinical_drawer_button_text": "Clinical Trials",
            "clinical_drawer_title": "",
            "clinical_drawer_body": "",
            "clinical_drawer_bg_color": "#ffffff",
            "clinical_drawer_text_color": "#080b2b"
          }
        },
        "accordion_who_is_this_for": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "WHO IS THIS FOR",
            "content": "<p>Balance Gum delivers a simple, sugar-free habit for anyone who wants to supportenergy, circulation, and oral health without adding another pill to their routine.It's the easiest place to start building a Nitric Oxide habit today.<br/><br/>Especially helpful as a pre-workout or midday pick-me-up. It can also complement the Berkeley Life Nitric Oxide Foundation supplement by supporting Nitric Oxide levels straight from the mouth, where the conversion process begins.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "clinical_drawer_button_text": "Clinical Trials",
            "clinical_drawer_title": "",
            "clinical_drawer_body": "",
            "clinical_drawer_bg_color": "#ffffff",
